Doris Fuller's daughter Natalie was diagnosed with bipolar disorder and psychosis at 22 . 
  She died last month after stepping in front of a train in Baltimore . 
  Natalie was not diagnosed until she was in her early 20s - and her illness went undiagnosed until then . 
  Mother said she was 'the bravest person I have ever known' and suffered from psychosis and bipolar disorder . 
  She said Natalie relapsed when she stopped taking her medication . 
 